<title type="html"><![CDATA[CHR-RAM or CHR-ROM? That is the question]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1251&amp;p=11057#p11057"><![CDATA[
Megaman 1 does upload tiles during levels.<br />And yeah, Megaman is a good comparaison between CHRAM and CHROM because even ones uses CHRAM and odd ones CHROM (with the exeption of the original, wich is CHRAM). Does Megaman 3 and 5 looks better than 4 and 6 ? I don't think so. There isn't THAT much difference. What I like with CHRAM is the ability to totally customize your tileset.<br />If you're writing a small game (NROM or CNROM), you'll want to go with CHROM. If you're going for a larger game, it all depend of the mapper and of the graphic features you want. I don't think one is better than the other (while I kinda like CHRAM, hehe).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Tue Mar 21, 2006 1:42 pm</p><hr />
